  <exercise permid="Jvd">
    <statement>
      <p permid="yfa">
        Let <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, and <m>C</m> be sets.

        <ol permid="gSu">
          <li permid="LUk">
            Find <m>\card{(A \cup C)\setminus B}</m> provided
            <m>\card{A} = 50</m>, <m>\card{B} = 45</m>,
            <m>\card{C} = 40</m>, <m>\card{A\cap B} = 20</m>,
            <m>\card{A \cap C} = 15</m>,
            <m>\card{B \cap C} = 23</m>, and <m>\card{A \cap B \cap C} = 12</m>.
          </li>

          <li permid="sbt">
            Describe a set in terms of <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>,
            and <m>C</m> with cardinality 26.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <hint permid="Lkq">
      <p permid="rFU">
        For part (a) you could use the formula for PIE, but for part (b) you might be better off drawing a Venn diagram.
      </p>
    </hint>
  </exercise>

